<div id="review_900852222" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/900852222" />
    <a title="Brandi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/344353-brandi"><img alt="Brandi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1242067188p2/344353.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/900852222?book_show_action=true">Apr 04, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brandi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brandi" href="/user/show/344353-brandi">Brandi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer900852222" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16892157043972015286">This book features some of the worst language I&apos;ve read since &quot;Twilight.&quot; That old &quot;show, don&apos;t tell&quot; rule of creative writing doesn&apos;t apply here. I held on for the rumored amazing plot twist but felt mostly irritated by the book at its end. Plus there&apos;s a tinge of old-fashioned ignorance and bigotry. Not good at all. As some other reviewers stated, this is the first major letdown I&apos;ve had on Goodreads reviews. I&apos;d be fine with my dog eating this book.</span>
  <span id="freeText16892157043972015286" style="display:none">This book features some of the worst language I've read since "Twilight." That old "show, don't tell" rule of creative writing doesn't apply here. I held on for the rumored amazing plot twist but felt mostly irritated by the book at its end. Plus there's a tinge of old-fashioned ignorance and bigotry. Not good at all. As some other reviewers stated, this is the first major letdown I've had on Goodreads reviews. I'd be fine with my dog eating this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16892157043972015286" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


